      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2023-04-20</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2023-05-04T15:31:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p> <strong>Prevent Family Fire Act of 2023 </strong></p> <p>This bill allows through 2030 a new tax credit equal to 10% of amounts received from the first retail sale of a safe firearm storage device, not to exceed $400 per device. </p> <p>The bill defines<em> safe firearm storage device</em> as a device that is designed and marketed to deny unauthorized access to, or render inoperable, a firearm or ammunition, and is secured by a combination lock, key lock, or lock based on biometric information.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
